- @simplewebauthn/server
- @simplewebauthn/browser

Important Project Rules
This project uses Next.js 16. Before changing Next.js APIs or route conventions, read the local Next docs under node_modules/next/dist/docs/.

Always use the existing DB helper:

import { query } from "@/lib/db";

Do not create neonPool.js or a second DB client.

Do not break:
- Login/auth
- JWT cookie flow
- Existing role redirects
- The Amardip blue mobile dashboard style
- Existing customer page/list
- Login page logo usage
- Existing username/password login fallback

Mobile App UX Rule
The admin dashboard is a mobile application shell, not a normal multi-page desktop website. Prefer opening modules inside the same app shell using dashboard tabs/subtabs. Do not use window.open or new browser tabs from dashboard cards unless the user explicitly asks for it. The standalone /admin/* pages can exist for direct access, but primary dashboard navigation should feel like one mobile app.

Always keep the app feel first. Avoid desktop-style redesigns, wide dashboard-first layouts, or opening separate tabs for normal workflows. Pages can support desktop/tablet with horizontal tables, but the primary experience should feel like a mobile admin app.

