user_passkeys table:
- id SERIAL primary key
- user_id INTEGER references users(id) on delete cascade
- credential_id TEXT unique
- credential_public_key TEXT
- counter BIGINT
- credential_device_type TEXT
- credential_backed_up BOOLEAN
- transports TEXT[]
- device_name TEXT
- created_at timestamptz
- last_used_at timestamptz

webauthn_challenges table:
- id SERIAL primary key
- user_id INTEGER references users(id) on delete cascade
- challenge TEXT
- challenge_type TEXT
- flow_id TEXT unique
- username TEXT
- expires_at timestamptz
- created_at timestamptz

Passkey API rules:
- Register/login/remove passkey APIs are POST only.
- /api/auth/passkey/list is GET only.
- Registration APIs require existing logged-in user from getUserFromRequest.
- Login options can accept username or allow discoverable passkey login if username is empty.
- List API returns only current user's id, deviceName, createdAt, and lastUsedAt.
- Remove API deletes only the current user's credential by id.
- Challenges expire in 5 minutes.
- Delete expired challenges before creating a new challenge.
- Delete used challenges after verification.
- Do not cache passkey API responses.
- Service worker must not cache passkey/auth APIs.
- Use the same cookie security settings as the existing password login API.
- Verification keeps SimpleWebAuthn default user verification behavior.

