Push notification plumbing:
- New helper: lib/pushNotifications.js
- Browser helper: lib/pushClient.js
- App badge helper: lib/appBadge.js
- New UI card: components/ui/PushNotificationCard.jsx
- Test API: POST /api/push/test
- Push subscription API uses setup-safe push_subscriptions table creation.
- Push sending soft-fails when VAPID env values are missing so normal ERP workflows do not break.
- Admin, customer, technician, and store app shells subscribe to PWA push notifications when the browser allows it.
- Profile/settings screens in all portals now show an Enable/Test Push Notifications card.
- The Enable action is tap-driven so iPhone/Safari/Chrome treat it as a real user permission request.
- The Test action sends a real push notification to the currently logged-in user/device.
- The service worker increments the installed PWA app icon badge count whenever a push notification arrives.
- Clicking a notification clears the app icon badge count.
- Opening/clearing in-app notifications also clears the app icon badge count and resets the service worker stored badge counter.
- App icon notification count depends on browser/OS Badging API support and works only where the installed PWA/browser supports badges.
- Notifications are sent for:
  - Customer raises a ticket: admin/manager/front office roles are notified.
  - Admin assigns a complaint to a worker: assigned worker is notified.
  - Worker completes a job: admin/manager/front office roles are notified.
  - Worker completes a customer-linked job: customer is notified when customer_user_id exists.

Required production push env:
- NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY
- VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY
- VAPID_SUBJECT

